    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 3.5: ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS,
        ACCELERATOR PEDAL POSITION SENSOR/IVS SWITCH (APS/IVS) - ATA COMMUNICATIONS - INSTRUMENT CLUSTER DISPLAY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSTRUMENT CLUSTER DISPLAY</title>
        <para>The instrument cluster utilizes data on the ATA lines for the display of:</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Oil Pressure</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Tachometer (Engine Speed)</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Speedometer</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Coolant Temperature</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Battery Voltage</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>The data is transmitted on the same ATA link that supplies information to the EST and the WTEC
            transmission controller. A microprocessor in the instrument cluster converts the ATA data into signals that
            will drive the various gauges in the dash.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1901709" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg7281" filename="../figeg7/EG7281.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.18 Diagnostic/Programmable Connection Electrical Circuit Diagram</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>* - Refer to CTS 5122V Electrical Circuit Diagrams Publication</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
